column5: Hi Forum, i came across this on You Tube and wanted to share with y'all. The gentleman gets a topwater strike out of his kayak big bass. Wondering out of curiosity how much would you all think this would weigh in at ?
i would say 10lbs + typical florida strain bass. they get hawgs over that way
That fish would weigh alot.  9+ maybe more.  that is a viscious hit.  wow.
I,de love to catch a bass like that .. those frog lures of his look awsome .
IMO it looks closer to 7, maybe 8 lb max.  Everyone will have their guess but no one is correct unless we see a scale.
too much of an ad for some product for me to bother watching
So I wasn't the only one that noticed....

I'd like to try one of the lures out but the price is insane, and I thought LiveTarget frogs were pricey  They look great and are handmade but I'd be tossing those with VERY heavy leaders to avoid any breakoffs, esp with pike.
Hey guys - on a scale of 1-10, how pretty is this girl?
Before or after the beer?  And yeah, it's another of those questions.

Hi there just want to let you know its not the frog im trying to show off but more the topwater strike....as for frogs i personally use 30 lb Power Pro with, the Live Target Frog in Black with Chartreuse, works great for pike and bass in Frenchman's Bay (Pickering Ont)
LOL, just big enough to get people to buy what he is selling?
